    {
      "id": "f715ce7b_ae8a77b1",
      "file_path": "policy-db-migrator/src/main/docker/db-migrator",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 502,
      "message": "hmm.  Actually, looks like it doesn't support \"<\" either (it interprets it as a redirect); the only string comparisons it supports are \"=\" and \"!=\".  One way around it is to use \"expr\" which can do the string comparison.  However, at this point, I think your original idea of extracting the numeric portion may be the best approach.  Should probably add a comment before this line that we have to compare the numeric portion because bourne shell doesn't support string comparison.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 811,
        "name": "Jim Hahn",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "jrh3@att.com",
        "username": "jrh3"
      },
